The paper deals with complexity classes and their complete problems, which are typically studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of formal language theory and polynomials suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO). The discussion of hierarchies and reductions may also relate to computational geometry (cs.CG) and scientific computing (cs.SC).
